ght policies and charitable emergency relief to guarantee household food security. Alternative policies and strategies of public action directed at the abolition of hunger are discussed. The publication of First World Hunger is a timely and important contribution to the debate about hunger and poverty in advanced market economies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aCoursebook. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh1 aCraig, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowler, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoppendieck, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiches, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiches, Graham, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUttler, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144260259540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442602595423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442602595.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK